{
  "id": "019d286a-f2d8-78b2-92cd-41ef0fe3537a",
  "content": "### Fix 3: Declaration + Usage Tracking (D74)\n\n  ```\n  ChunkRelation {\n      from_source_file: <usage chunk's file>,\n      from_start_line: <usage chunk's start line>,\n      relation: \"uses\",\n      to_file: <definition chunk's file>,\n      to_name: Some(<symbol name>),\n  }\n  ```\n- If a symbol is defined in multiple files (e.g., re-exports), link to all definitions\n- If a symbol appears in 10+ files, skip it (too generic, would create edge explosion)\n\n**Integration:**\n- Called from `process_batch()` after chunks are processed\n- Returns extra `ChunkRelation` entries appended to the existing relations vec\n- `wire_pipeline_relations()` in CLI handles them identically\n\n**Expected yield:** 200-400 new `\"uses\"` edges connecting implementations to trait/type definitions across crate boundaries.\n\n**Alternatives rejected:**\n- (A) Symbol index (co-reference) — simpler but creates undirected edges without definition/usage semantics\n- (C) Embedding similarity — computationally expensive (O(n²)) and less interpretable\n\n---\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-04-m3.4-graph-edge-improvements-design.md",
